name: DJ Sabrina the Teenage DJ
description:
'''DJ Sabrina the Teenage DJ''' (abbreviated '''DJSTTDJ''') is a pseudonymous [[London]]-based [[Electronic music|electronic]] producer. Her name is a reference to the television sitcom ''[[Sabrina the Teenage Witch (1996 TV series)|Sabrina the Teenage Witch]]'', inspired by a comment on [[YouTube]]. She released her debut album, ''Makin' Magick'', in 2017. Her main musical influences include [[plunderphonics]] musicians and the 2010s UK [[outsider house]] scene.

DJ Sabrina collaborated with her sibling Salem on ''Makin' Magick'', which led to Salem being credited as a member of a duo with Sabrina by some media outlets. "[T]he bio has always mentioned Sabrina and Salem, but I like the idea of it being a mystery," the artist has stated.
